    "body": "See thread starting at http://codespeak.net/pipermail/cython-dev/2009-November/007666.html\n\nOne thing to note is that since python modules don't get unloaded, without starting a new python process we can't test both c and cpp in the same run. \n\nThis ticket is to resolve the issue for 0.12, a real fix may be deferred for later. \n\nMigrated from http://trac.cython.org/ticket/449",
    "closed_at": "2009-11-17T19:12:45Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "@robertwb changed **owner** to `robertwb`\ncommented\n\nhttp://hg.cython.org/cython-devel/rev/06d71d66fb4a\n\nThere were two issues here. First, it was trying to pickle a function, and this error was ignored in the child side and so the parent side blocked trying to read and unwritten pipe. Second, pipes have a finite buffer, so if there were a lot of errors than the child would block on writing before the parent read anything (because the parent was set to wait until the child finished). I've worked around this issue by using temp files rather than pipes, which isn't as elegant but won't suffer from the same issues. (Theoretically one could start reading before the child has terminated, but that may have other issues.) ",
            "created_at": "2009-11-17T19:12:40Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/1010#issuecomment-240046228",
